
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `corelist` baraye fahmidane inke aya yek module Perl ba version-e asli Perl hamrah ast ya na, estefade mishavad.  Be zabane sade, be shoma miguyad aya niaz hast yek module ra nasb konid ya an dar hale hazer dar Perl-e shoma vojud darad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `corelist MojulName` -->  📃 Check mikonad aya MojulName dar version-e asli Perl vojud darad.
    🔹 `corelist -v 5.10 MojulName` --> 🔍 Check mikonad aya MojulName dar version-e moshakhas-e Perl (dar inja, 5.10) vojud darad.
    🔹 `corelist -a MojulName` --> 📊 Hameye version-haye Perl ra neshon midahad ke MojulName dar anha vojud dashte ast.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ corelist Module::Name

    🔹 Check mikonad aya Module::Name dar version-e asli Perl shoma vojud darad.

    $ corelist -v 5.26 JSON

    🔹 Check mikonad aya mojule JSON dar version-e 5.26 Perl vojud dashte ast.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ corelist Time::Piece

    🔹 Agar `Time::Piece` ba Perl shoma hamrah bashad, version-e Perl ra neshon midahad. Agar hamrah nabashad, peyghami ra neshon midahad ke an module dar version-e asli nist.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `corelist` command is used to determine if a Perl module is bundled with a standard Perl distribution.  Simply put, it tells you whether you need to install a module, or if it's already included with your Perl installation.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `corelist ModuleName` --> 📃 Checks if ModuleName is included in the default Perl version.
    🔹 `corelist -v 5.10 ModuleName` --> 🔍 Checks if ModuleName was included in a specific Perl version (here, 5.10).
    🔹 `corelist -a ModuleName` --> 📊 Shows all Perl versions in which ModuleName was included.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ corelist Module::Name

    🔹 Checks if Module::Name is included in your default Perl version.

    $ corelist -v 5.26 JSON

    🔹 Checks if the JSON module was included in Perl version 5.26.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ corelist Time::Piece

    🔹 If `Time::Piece` is bundled with your Perl, it will output the Perl version number. Otherwise, it will output a message indicating that the module is not core.

